SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 584
By Roberts
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Janice Gammon of
Orlinda.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Janice Gammon of Orlinda; and
WHEREAS, Jan Gammon was an exemplary public servant and consummate
professional who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for her fellow citizens in
numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Gammon was the daughter of the late Keith and Margie Hitson, and for
four decades, she helped make a home on her family's dairy farm, where she worked tirelessly
as an active farmhand and milkmaid; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Gammon found great joy in gardening, canning, and cooking; she was
known for her generous spirit and her love for sharing meals with others, and she always
ensured that family members and farmhands alike were well fed; and
WHEREAS, deeply committed to public service, Jan Gammon was instrumental in
establishing the Robertson County Republican Party; she served as State Executive Committee
Woman for the 18th Senatorial District, a member of the Tennessee Board of Professional
Responsibility, and as a Robertson County Commissioner, a position in which she served for
twelve years; and
WHEREAS, most recently, Mrs. Gammon was honored at the Reagan Day Dinner in
Robertson County, an event she helped to establish; she was renowned in the political
landscape for her honest counsel, encouragement, and wisdom shaped by her years of
experience and conviction; and
SJR0584
011069
- 1 -

WHEREAS, a woman of deep and abiding faith, Mrs. Gammon was an active member at
Station Camp Baptist Church, where she was proud to play an important role in helping people
in their walk in faith through guidance and prayer; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Gammon was also deeply devoted to her family, and she always
endeavored to remain true to family values of the highest order; and
WHEREAS, left to cherish her memory are her beloved husband of fifty-nine years,
Bobby Gammon; her children, Robert Keith Gammon, Sherri (David) Ferguson, and Steven
(Shonda) Gammon; her grandchildren, Chelsea (Rusty) Fuqua, Alex (Heather) Ferguson, Brett
(Katie) Ferguson, Katie (Drew) Green, Ginia Gammon, Chase Gammon, and Cooper Gammon;
her great-grandchildren, Gracey, Gabi, Dawson, Demi, Ridge, Sawyer, Andrew, and Thomas;
her sisters, Yvonne Beaver and Patricia Owens; and her daughter-in-law, Trena Gammon; and
WHEREAS, the epitome of gratitude, admiration, and love, Jan Gammon was a wise
soul who impacted the lives of those who were blessed to know her; she leaves behind an
indelible legacy of integrity and probity in public life, compassion and loyalty in private life, and
diligence and dedication in all her chosen endeavors; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
remember the bountiful life of this exceptional public servant and human being; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of Janice Gammon, reflecting
fondly upon her impeccable character and her stalwart commitment to living the examined life
with courage and conviction.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we extend our sympathy and offer our condolences
to the family of Mrs. Gammon.
- 2 - 011069

BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
